el=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gulfcoastsailingschool.com/uploads/4/6/8/6/46860537/constant_bearing_-_decreasing_range.pdf\">\"Collision Course with a Crossing  Boat? How to Know\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. Gulf Coast Sailing School<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">18 August</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Collision+Course+with+a+Crossing++Boat%3F+How+to+Know&amp;rft.pub=Gulf+Coast+Sailing+School&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gulfcoastsailingschool.com%2Fuploads%2F4%2F6%2F8%2F6%2F46860537%2Fconstant_bearing_-_decreasing_range.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AConstant+bearing%2C+decreasing+range\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Smith-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Smith_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Smith, Gregory L. (Captain) (February 2017). \"For river pilots, tri-sectoring most effective way to determine collision risk\". <i>Professional Mariner</i> (February 2017).</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Professional+Mariner&amp;rft.atitle=For+river+pilots%2C+tri-sectoring+most+effective+way+to+determine+collision+risk&amp;rft.issue=February+2017&amp;rft.date=2017-02&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Gregory+L.+%28Captain%29&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AConstant+bearing%2C+decreasing+range\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1258\nCached time: 20180908153928\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.099 seconds\nPreprocessor vis